e can be your most valuable asset as long as you don''t aim it at yourself.', 25459, 0), (134372, 'He blushed to see other Frenchmen overcome with joy whenever they met a compatriot abroad. The would fall on each other, cluster in a raucous group, and pass whole evenings complaining about the barbarity of the locals. These were the few who actually noticed that locals did things differently. Others managed to travel so ‘covered and wrapped in a taciturn and incommunicative prudence, defending themselves from the contagion of an unknown atmosphere’ that they noticed nothing at all.', 25621, 0), (134373, 'Creativity and expression of one’s art can only be measured by the audience to whom it was intended for.  Not everyone is going to like my “art” and I don’t really care about that.', 25619, 0), (134374, 'Many years ago, I left my home country very narrow minded. Today I return with an educated mind, able to understand why my culture is as it is and still be very proud of it.', 9382, 0), (134375, 'I am also open minded to embrace strange notions and respect its bearers without harsh judgement. Exposure has made me feel confident and wiser to choose what feels right for me, in order to be the best human being for myself and others.', 9382, 0), (134376, 'Being able to experience and live the differences with sound judgement offers a chance to opt for what is right for one.', 9382, 0), (134377, 'Dont forget to pray today, because God didn''t forget to wake you up this morning.', 25622, 0), (134378, 'Do not fear to find yourself among strangers.', 9382, 0), (134379, 'What might be considered loyalty in onesociety might not necessarily be the same for another.', 9382, 0), (134380, 'Life at home is at a pace which allows you to appreciate what it has to offer. Simultaneously you get a chance to reflect on what you wish from it. Our development also goes at the same pace, which is not something that everyone appreciates.', 9382, 0), (134381, 'Then I learnt of “white Christma